  "title": "Testing HTTP status codes with pytest (Python 3.12+)",
  "summary": "This guide provides a comprehensive explanation on how to test HTTP status codes using pytest, the popular Python testing framework, in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "Leverage Python's built-in `requests` library for sending HTTP requests during tests.",
    "Assert on the returned HTTP status code to validate expected responses.",
    "Use pytest fixtures for setting up and teardown of common resources (e.g., test servers).",
    "Employ pytest markers to group related tests based on their intended HTTP status codes."
  ],

